                    </div>
                </section>
                <section>
                    <h2>Common Issues and Solutions</h2>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            <h3>Nodemon Not Found</h3>
                            <p><strong>Issue:</strong> The command
                                <code>nodemon</code> is not recognized.</p>
                            <p><strong>Solution:</strong> Ensure Nodemon is
                                installed globally or locally in your
                                project.</p>
                            <pre><code># Install Nodemon globally
npm install -g nodemon

# Or install Nodemon locally in your project
npm install --save-dev nodemon
                        </code></pre>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <h3>Permission Errors</h3>
                            <p><strong>Issue:</strong> Permission denied when
                                trying to run Nodemon.</p>
                            <p><strong>Solution:</strong> Use <code>sudo</code>
                                to install Nodemon globally or change the
                                permissions.</p>
                            <pre><code># Using sudo for global installation
sudo npm install -g nodemon

# Changing directory permissions
sudo chown -R $(whoami) $(npm config get prefix)/{lib/node_modules,bin,share}
                        </code></pre>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <h3>Nodemon Not Restarting on File Changes</h3>
                            <p><strong>Issue:</strong> Nodemon does not restart
                                the application when files change.</p>
                            <p><strong>Solution:</strong> Ensure the correct
                                file extensions are being watched and check the
                                Nodemon configuration.</p>
                            <pre><code>// Add a nodemon.json file to your project root
{
  "watch": ["src"],
  "ext": "js,json",
  "ignore": ["src/public"]
}
                        </code></pre>
                            <p>Alternatively, use the command line options:</p>
                            <pre><code>nodemon --watch src --ext js,json
                        </code></pre>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <h3>Compatibility Issues with Node.js Version</h3>
                            <p><strong>Issue:</strong> Nodemon behaves
                                unexpectedly with certain Node.js versions.</p>
                            <p><strong>Solution:</strong> Ensure your Node.js
                                version is compatible with Nodemon.</p>
                            <pre><code># Check your Node.js version
node -v

# Update Node.js if necessary
nvm install node
                        </code></pre>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <h3>Nodemon Crashes on Startup</h3>
                            <p><strong>Issue:</strong> Nodemon crashes
                                immediately after starting.</p>
                            <p><strong>Solution:</strong> Check for syntax
                                errors in your code or issues in the Nodemon
                                configuration.</p>
                            <pre><code># Run your application with node to check for errors
node yourApp.js

# If no errors, try running Nodemon in debug mode
nodemon --verbose yourApp.js
                        </code></pre>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </section>
